Postoperative fever is a temperature higher than 102.2 F on any day after surgery or 100.4 F on any two consecutive days after surgery. Fever after surgery is very common. Most cases are harmless and go away on their own. 

However, If you have any of the following signs of infection after your surgery, let your doctor know: 

🔥 Fever higher than 101 F. 
🔥Pus or more drainage from your incision
🔥More swelling
🔥Redness or warmth at the site of your incision
🔥A foul smell coming from the incision‌

You should also call if you're coughing up or vomiting blood, or if you have: 

🔥Severe headache or other pain
🔥Loss of appetite
🔥Problems breathing
🔥Redness or pain near your incision
🔥Constipation or diarrhea
🔥Very tired feeling‌

Even if you don't have any of the symptoms above, call your doctor if you just generally feel worse than when you left the hospital, or if you have any other symptoms that concern you.

Don’t skip your lymphatic massages!
These gentle and targeted lymphatic massages help your body’s lymphatic system flush out toxins, excess fluids, reduce swelling, and promote healing. 

By stimulating lymphatic circulation, you can enhance your recovery process, minimize discomfort, and unveil your beautiful new contours sooner! All
Lymphatic massages help prevent or minimize the development of fibrosis, allowing for better tissue healing and a more desirable outcome.
They also can boost the immune system by improving lymphatic flow, which plays a crucial role in carrying immune cells throughout the body. This can contribute to a healthier recovery and overall well-being.
